WEBVTT

00:04.790 --> 00:06.690
[man]
<i>Previously on</i> Billions...

00:06.890 --> 00:07.740
[Chuck] Mr. Andolov,

00:07.940 --> 00:09.220
My first act as attorney
general

00:09.420 --> 00:12.370
was to freeze your funds
in the United States.

00:12.570 --> 00:15.510
<i>My second act is inviting you </i>
<i>to leave our sunny shores. </i>

00:15.710 --> 00:19.790
I, of course, picked up
the scent of the Axelrod

00:19.990 --> 00:20.920
behind this.

00:21.120 --> 00:22.900
Charles Rhodes, Jr.
is hereby removed

00:23.100 --> 00:24.750
as attorney general
of the state of New York.

00:24.950 --> 00:28.050
[Chuck] <i>Everywhere </i>
<i>he goes, we are watching. </i>

00:28.250 --> 00:29.860
It's hard to march
toward the presidency

00:30.060 --> 00:31.640
when you're always
looking over your shoulder.

00:31.830 --> 00:32.910
The beginnings of a plan.

00:33.110 --> 00:34.620
Secrecy and deception.

00:34.820 --> 00:35.870
I'm starting to get misty.

00:36.070 --> 00:37.660
Jesus.
You like shaking people up.

00:37.860 --> 00:38.950
Like it? I don't know.

00:39.160 --> 00:39.960
It just happens.

00:40.160 --> 00:41.230
I love that you're loyal

00:41.430 --> 00:43.190
until I help
get you elected to Congress.

00:43.390 --> 00:45.250
[Chuck]
You've accumulated so much,

00:45.450 --> 00:47.050
you think laws
don't apply to you?

00:47.250 --> 00:49.900
Who appointed you the keeper
of these cosmic rules

00:50.100 --> 00:51.150
in the first place?

00:51.350 --> 00:53.090
<i>The fucking arrogance! </i>

01:01.350 --> 01:05.270


01:15.530 --> 01:18.070


01:33.000 --> 01:35.090
[sighs]
Oh, I've always wanted

01:35.290 --> 01:37.080
to see
Vestmannaeyjar in the dark.

01:37.280 --> 01:40.640
Best way for a newly installed
U.S. Attorney not to be tracked.

01:40.840 --> 01:43.710
And for an international
fugitive not to be extradited.

01:43.910 --> 01:44.980
Something for everyone.

01:45.180 --> 01:46.980
Lay it out for me.

01:47.180 --> 01:48.690
I've been told
I needed to see you.

01:48.890 --> 01:51.130
When Wendy wants something,
she's very persuasive.

01:51.330 --> 01:53.270
Eh, that's why I called her.

01:54.280 --> 01:56.950
I need safe passage to America.

01:57.150 --> 02:00.280
- For you?
- No, not for me.

02:03.030 --> 02:04.140
I'll need a name, Robert.

02:04.340 --> 02:07.000
Yeah, Charles,
I'm working up to it.

02:07.200 --> 02:08.790
Is that because
I'm going to hate it?

02:08.990 --> 02:11.460
Well, you ain't gonna love it.

02:17.300 --> 02:20.720
[speaking Ukranian]

02:39.700 --> 02:42.320
[man speaking Ukranian]

02:47.080 --> 02:49.910
[tense music playing]

03:41.260 --> 03:44.720
Vasily Melnikov, stabbed.

03:45.350 --> 03:47.930
Vladislav Avayev, shot.

03:48.560 --> 03:51.770
Sergey Protosenya, hanged.

03:52.940 --> 03:56.240
Alexander Tyulyakov,
also hanged.

03:56.440 --> 03:59.090
And the list goes on.

03:59.290 --> 04:04.410
All friends and colleagues
of mine. All dead.

04:06.030 --> 04:07.270
[Axe] My condolences.

04:07.470 --> 04:10.040
Dangerous time
to be an oligarch.

04:10.240 --> 04:13.020
[Grigor]
Yet when you called and asked,

04:13.220 --> 04:15.250
even though we had agreed

04:15.450 --> 04:18.860
you would stay out
of my part of the world,

04:19.060 --> 04:21.390
I helped you anyway.

04:21.590 --> 04:23.200
Helped me?

04:23.400 --> 04:25.060
No, we both worked together

04:25.260 --> 04:28.100
to help the man
in the olive drab t-shirt.

04:28.300 --> 04:31.480
Because both he
and his country needed it.

04:31.680 --> 04:33.130
- Yours, too.
- Hmm.

04:33.330 --> 04:36.210
Not how the Kremlin sees it.

04:36.410 --> 04:37.880
[Axe]
That's how you see it.

04:38.080 --> 04:40.930
You know, it's no good being
a citizen, even a rich one,

04:41.130 --> 04:43.890
from a country
that's isolated, bled dry.

04:44.090 --> 04:47.140
Well, like how I felt
when you chased me

04:47.340 --> 04:49.480
out of the United States.

04:49.680 --> 04:52.120
Ah, that's semi-ancient
history.

04:52.320 --> 04:55.340
Now you have freedom here
in Europe. We both do.

04:55.540 --> 04:58.940
To walk the streets.
To wet our beaks.

04:59.140 --> 05:01.300
Thanks to the arms
that I financed,

05:01.500 --> 05:03.010
and you sourced.

05:03.210 --> 05:07.370
And you think this
wipes our ledger clean?

05:07.570 --> 05:10.330
Oh, did I forget to send you
a fucking fruit basket?

05:10.530 --> 05:15.590
Oh, a few kumquats is not
going to change anything.

05:15.790 --> 05:18.440
But our ledger is not clean.

05:18.640 --> 05:23.110
It is like a windshield
that was tended to

05:23.310 --> 05:26.720
by your... [squeaking sounds]

05:26.920 --> 05:31.250
....squeegee men that thrived
under your Mayor Dinkins.

05:31.450 --> 05:34.850
All the showy effort
and noise,

05:35.050 --> 05:40.210
and still, windshield
covered in grime and dirt.

05:40.410 --> 05:44.680
Until I am rehabilitated
in the United States,

05:44.880 --> 05:46.200
we are not square.

05:46.400 --> 05:48.160
I'm not even rehabilitated
there.

05:48.360 --> 05:50.270
And I'm not a foreign national.
You are.

05:50.470 --> 05:53.420
And I am the one
defying my government

05:53.610 --> 05:57.630
during a purge
that makes Joe Stalin

05:57.830 --> 06:01.210
look like Joan fucking Baez.

06:01.410 --> 06:05.530
If my loyalty
is even questioned

06:05.730 --> 06:07.850
by the leaders of my country--

06:08.050 --> 06:10.370
I get it. You go on
the dead oligarch list.

06:10.570 --> 06:12.660
Hm. So now...

06:13.660 --> 06:14.810
to what I need.

06:15.010 --> 06:19.190
And what you will
deliver on a platter.

06:19.390 --> 06:22.590
I need to return to America.

06:22.790 --> 06:25.340
On a deeply personal mission.

06:25.540 --> 06:28.530
You do know that
all your funds are frozen?

06:28.730 --> 06:30.580
Down to the last kopek.

06:30.780 --> 06:33.120
Plus, you're on
a sanctions list.

06:33.320 --> 06:35.330
No matter what the mission,

06:35.530 --> 06:37.210
I suggest you conduct it
somewhere else.

06:37.410 --> 06:38.310
[Grigor] No, Axe.

06:38.510 --> 06:43.280
You will arrange it
so I can walk back in,

06:43.480 --> 06:45.220
do my business freely,

06:45.420 --> 06:50.350
and in return,
I will grant something to you.

06:50.550 --> 06:53.450
Could be tickets to the
Bolshoi,

06:53.650 --> 06:56.020
could be to allow you

06:56.220 --> 06:58.100
to keep walking around here,

06:58.300 --> 07:00.380
breathing freely.

07:00.580 --> 07:02.360
Threats? Really?

07:02.560 --> 07:06.550
What in my history makes you
think I respond well to threats?

07:06.750 --> 07:09.470
What in my history
makes you think

07:09.670 --> 07:12.100
it's merely a threat?

07:12.300 --> 07:15.100


07:17.100 --> 07:19.210
[Chuck]
Grigor Andolov.

07:19.410 --> 07:21.040
It's within your authority,

07:21.240 --> 07:23.280
within your ability
to figure it out anyway.

07:23.480 --> 07:25.490
[Chuck] To give
an exiled criminal a visa?

07:25.690 --> 07:26.650
So he can, what,

07:26.850 --> 07:29.050
muscle in on the Brighton Beach
heroin trade?

07:29.250 --> 07:30.550
Fuck with our next election?

07:30.750 --> 07:32.950
[Axe]
His wife's still in New York.

07:33.150 --> 07:35.640
She's suing for divorce
on grounds of abandonment.

07:35.840 --> 07:37.690
Well, maybe he can
countersue for irony.

07:37.890 --> 07:41.110
And if he can't even show up...

07:41.310 --> 07:43.050
she gets a default judgment
worth billions.

07:43.250 --> 07:47.460
Oh! Now we're talking
your love language.

07:48.630 --> 07:50.320
This is important to me.

07:50.520 --> 07:52.050
Important to you.

07:52.250 --> 07:53.450
To the man who defied me

07:53.650 --> 07:55.140
on that heliport
not so long ago?

07:55.340 --> 07:59.350
[scoffs] I would consider it
a personal favor.

07:59.550 --> 08:01.310
When Ali was broke,
could no longer fight,

08:01.510 --> 08:02.980
couldn't even
pick up his dinner tab,

08:03.180 --> 08:05.000
Smoking Joe
hauled him into his limo,

08:05.200 --> 08:07.070
counted out a thousand bucks,
cash.

08:07.270 --> 08:10.260
Sure, the old combatants code.

08:10.460 --> 08:12.450
But based on the shiny new
G800,

08:12.650 --> 08:14.280
plenty of purses
rolling your way.

08:14.480 --> 08:16.660
Yeah, I'm flush.

08:16.860 --> 08:18.350
So I'll make you an offer.

08:18.550 --> 08:20.270
You get Grigor to the U.S.,

08:20.470 --> 08:22.420
I'll owe you a debt.

08:22.620 --> 08:25.360
You do remember when I kicked
him out of there, that, too,

08:25.560 --> 08:26.550
was a favor to you?

08:26.750 --> 08:28.070
Yeah, it's all more perplexing

08:28.270 --> 08:29.530
than the betrayal
of Johnny Caspar.

08:29.730 --> 08:30.680
But I need it done.

08:30.880 --> 08:32.320
So if you do it,

08:32.520 --> 08:35.410
I promise that I will come
through for you when you ask.

08:35.610 --> 08:38.350
And I think you know,
when I make a promise,

08:38.550 --> 08:41.100
I don't come up short.

08:43.940 --> 08:45.560
[dry chuckle]

08:49.440 --> 08:50.840
[sighs] Well, I'll say it.

08:51.040 --> 08:52.490
We aren't breaking through.

08:52.690 --> 08:54.620
Yet you remain undefined

08:54.820 --> 08:56.310
beyond rich, smart, nice guy.

08:56.510 --> 08:59.350
The party primaries are sucking
up all the media attention.

08:59.550 --> 09:01.190
Do I have to fly
the National damn Guard

09:01.390 --> 09:02.870
every time
I want some political ink?

09:03.080 --> 09:04.440
Can you?

09:04.640 --> 09:05.500
I'm not laughing.

09:05.700 --> 09:07.150
What else has had
that type of impact,

09:07.350 --> 09:09.130
historically,
for an outsider candidate?

09:09.330 --> 09:11.740
The only independent to ever
really get traction was--

09:11.940 --> 09:14.010
Yes. Perot.

09:15.340 --> 09:16.370
I saw it as a kid.

09:16.570 --> 09:19.100
I buy a--a half hour
on every major network.

09:19.300 --> 09:21.080
- Live speech.
- Hm. It'll play like you're

09:21.280 --> 09:24.100
making an acceptance speech
at your own national convention.

09:24.300 --> 09:26.230
Yeah, we call that
the primetime roadblock.

09:26.430 --> 09:29.320
No way around us, we'll
reframe the entire race.

09:29.520 --> 09:31.990
How do you win
outside the system?

09:32.190 --> 09:35.350
You run as the antidote
to the system.

09:35.540 --> 09:37.370
The theme will be
taking inventory,

09:37.570 --> 09:38.540
looking inside ourselves

09:38.740 --> 09:40.250
to see how
we let things get this bad.

09:40.450 --> 09:43.540
Yes. Asking the hard,
honest questions

09:43.740 --> 09:46.110
no politician dares ask...

09:46.310 --> 09:49.170
to remake ourselves
in order to remake the country.

09:49.370 --> 09:50.320
Before it's too late.

09:50.520 --> 09:52.300
[Wags] The full Lincoln.
Do it the right way,

09:52.500 --> 09:53.760
the other candidates
will look like

09:53.960 --> 09:55.450
lawn jockeys
at the Belmont Stakes.

09:55.650 --> 09:56.510
[Wendy] Tell the story...

09:56.710 --> 09:57.720
of how you ask your people

09:57.920 --> 09:59.200
how <i>you</i> can do better,

09:59.400 --> 10:02.000
be better, as you
will also ask the country.

10:02.200 --> 10:03.560
I like that.

10:03.760 --> 10:06.040
Then you have to really do it.

10:06.240 --> 10:08.480
Solicit honest feedback
from your employees.

10:08.680 --> 10:11.530
Use it as fuel for the speech.

10:11.730 --> 10:12.630
Use it as an example.

10:12.830 --> 10:14.090
[Luke] Yeah, great.

10:14.290 --> 10:15.720
I'll run focus groups with
your people to get that info.

10:15.920 --> 10:17.010
[Prince] Hm.

10:17.210 --> 10:19.200
Boil it down to a lean
PowerPoint to present to you.

10:19.400 --> 10:20.490
I'm not sure inserting a layer

10:20.690 --> 10:22.620
between Mike and his guys
is the way to success.

10:22.820 --> 10:23.850
Happens to be the only way

10:24.050 --> 10:25.600
the political research
process works.

10:25.800 --> 10:26.880
Filters,
funnels, all of it.

10:27.080 --> 10:28.460
No, no, no.
I want the full fire hose.

10:28.660 --> 10:29.960
That's the point.
As Wendy says.

10:30.160 --> 10:31.360
Okay, how about this?

10:31.560 --> 10:33.300
I run the process
with Mike in the room.

10:33.500 --> 10:35.720
We make it authentic,
substantial.

10:35.920 --> 10:37.160
Full fat, full flavor.

10:37.360 --> 10:39.700
So Mike can eat it up
and then spit it out.

10:39.900 --> 10:41.790
We'd spend all week
Heimliching the guy.

10:41.990 --> 10:43.480
This has to be a battle cry.

10:43.680 --> 10:46.350
No, no, no time for
self-recrimination or anything

10:46.550 --> 10:47.830
that blunts
the tip of the sword.

10:48.030 --> 10:49.290
Like actual self-knowledge?

10:49.490 --> 10:50.550
I have to run this process.

10:50.740 --> 10:52.130
So you can baby-proof
the credenza.

10:52.330 --> 10:54.300
So I can keep out the noise.
Same process I used

10:54.500 --> 10:55.590
to elect a third of the Senate.

10:55.790 --> 10:56.930
Oh, the same guys
that are so out of touch,

10:57.130 --> 10:58.600
Mike had to step in
and run 'em out of town?

10:58.790 --> 11:00.490
I don't need my candidate
picking pepper out of fly shit

11:00.690 --> 11:02.450
- on the eve of a major speech.
- [Prince] I've heard enough.

11:02.650 --> 11:04.770
Brad, you can run the process
with me in the room.

11:04.970 --> 11:08.330
Wendy'll be there, too.
Team of rivals.

11:08.530 --> 11:11.210
Make the buy,
set the meeting.

11:14.540 --> 11:15.780


11:15.980 --> 11:17.910
[door opens]

11:18.110 --> 11:20.720
[sighs]

11:20.920 --> 11:25.100
We are gonna do something
extremely hard.

11:26.180 --> 11:27.670
[Ira] Um, great?

11:27.870 --> 11:30.750
[sighs] Yeah, everyone's
gonna be angry about it.

11:30.950 --> 11:33.960
It'll cause enormous tension
with Washington,

11:34.160 --> 11:35.530
with Albany, too.

11:35.730 --> 11:38.430
Sounds horrible.
What's it entail?

11:38.630 --> 11:40.740
Getting a previously
ejected oligarch

11:40.940 --> 11:42.390
back into the country.

11:42.590 --> 11:43.950
- A Russian oligarch?
- [Chuck] Mm-hmm.

11:44.150 --> 11:45.730
One with a big red
target on his back.

11:45.920 --> 11:50.060
From DOJ, from DHS,
from Interpol, too.

11:50.260 --> 11:52.360
Grigor Andolov.

11:52.560 --> 11:54.340
And you want to do this now,

11:54.540 --> 11:56.400
during the second coming
of the Red Menace.

11:56.600 --> 11:58.680
Like I said, extremely hard.

11:58.880 --> 12:00.030
If it's doable at all.

12:00.230 --> 12:02.410
Why would you even consider it?

12:02.610 --> 12:05.800
As a favor to Bobby Axelrod.

12:06.720 --> 12:07.930
Those words just
tumbled out of your mouth

12:08.130 --> 12:09.350
like a meth addict's teeth...

12:09.550 --> 12:11.100
- [sighs]
- ...and just as fucked up.

12:11.300 --> 12:14.210
[stammers] How do you
figure you'll pull this off?

12:14.410 --> 12:17.320
I have to talk
to a special advisor.

12:17.520 --> 12:19.400
- Big man in certain circles.
- [door opens]

12:19.600 --> 12:22.350
Bunky Stevens
is going to be a father

12:22.540 --> 12:25.560
with his third wife, Candy.

12:25.760 --> 12:27.500
Neat trick,
considering he died

12:27.700 --> 12:29.600
- a few months back.
- [Swerdlow] Mm-mm.

12:29.800 --> 12:31.830
Post-mortem
jizz retrieval, you dig?

12:32.030 --> 12:32.920
Not sure I do.

12:33.120 --> 12:34.590
[Swerdlow] Well, you get
the stiff on the table,

12:34.790 --> 12:36.170
even though
he ain't so stiff no more.

12:36.370 --> 12:37.440
Get my drift?

12:37.640 --> 12:39.170
And then you
drain those berries.

12:39.370 --> 12:41.740
You do it soon enough, you
end up with viable swimmers,

12:41.940 --> 12:43.570
Jizz. Stuff of life.

12:43.770 --> 12:45.430
[Chuck Sr.]
Stuff of fraud.

12:45.630 --> 12:48.580
There's a new fertility start-up
out there doing this.

12:48.780 --> 12:51.940
Candy is just beefing up
her claim on the estate.

12:52.140 --> 12:54.840
The first and second wives
will get nothing...

12:55.040 --> 12:56.500
now that there's
going to be an heir.

12:56.700 --> 12:58.740
No respect for the starter
wives in our culture,

12:58.940 --> 13:00.090
chicks who break the seal.

13:00.290 --> 13:01.510
In Thailand,
even the minor wives

13:01.710 --> 13:03.220
get one hell of
a birthday bunfight.

13:03.420 --> 13:04.470
Uh-huh.

13:04.670 --> 13:05.740
You're going to want
to think global

13:05.940 --> 13:07.060
but act local on this one.

13:07.260 --> 13:08.310
[Chuck] Mm.

13:08.510 --> 13:09.730
It's your worst nightmare,
isn't it?

13:09.930 --> 13:12.350
A paternity suit that
can't be settled out of court.

13:12.550 --> 13:15.400
Oh, it's a question of
basic fairness, don't you see?

13:15.600 --> 13:17.550
Never your concern.

13:17.750 --> 13:19.990
And I don't recall you
thinking much of

13:20.190 --> 13:21.840
Bunky or his wives, either.

13:22.040 --> 13:24.590
So the fact that you're
suddenly the guardian

13:24.790 --> 13:26.930
of the product
of his vas deferens,

13:27.130 --> 13:29.750
I know there's more
to the story.

13:29.950 --> 13:31.120
That mean that
you're not gonna

13:31.320 --> 13:32.890
club this company
into oblivion

13:33.090 --> 13:36.420
and seize the embryos that
result from this unholy process?

13:36.620 --> 13:37.880
It means I'll look into it,

13:38.080 --> 13:40.550
and decide what
I'll do as usual.

13:40.750 --> 13:41.900
Bye, Dad.

13:42.100 --> 13:44.450
Hey, sugar, you be getting
that shit I've been sending you?

13:44.650 --> 13:47.110
I have. And I thank you.

13:48.820 --> 13:50.950
[scoffs] It's, uh, uh,

13:51.150 --> 13:52.850
I guess it's what
you'd call PEDs,

13:53.050 --> 13:54.540
but in lozenge form.

13:54.740 --> 13:56.380
So, put it under your tongue.

13:56.580 --> 13:58.130
It hits the bloodstream
instantly.

13:58.330 --> 13:59.670
Like a ball-peen
fucking hammer.

13:59.870 --> 14:03.130
Turns any man into
a world-class sheet-athlete.

14:03.880 --> 14:04.930
Wonderful.

14:05.130 --> 14:06.720
[Chuck Sr.]
And I'm left wondering why

14:06.920 --> 14:09.740
none of this sublingual supreme
has been sent my way.

14:09.940 --> 14:12.100
For the simple reason it may
kill you, big papa,

14:12.300 --> 14:14.140
like Dirty Harry in '71.

14:24.020 --> 14:25.050
[door closes]

14:25.250 --> 14:27.490
He goes
into this speech confident,

14:27.690 --> 14:28.580
he comes out sailing.

14:28.780 --> 14:30.350
Zooming up the fucking polls.

14:30.550 --> 14:32.040
And we're just supposed
to stand there clapping

14:32.240 --> 14:34.440
like extras
in a Riefenstahl film.

14:34.640 --> 14:35.560
With Bradford running point,

14:35.760 --> 14:37.130
the feedbacks gonna be jet
fuel.

14:37.330 --> 14:38.960
[utensils clink]

14:40.500 --> 14:43.550
Uh, there is a potential
equal time issue.

14:43.750 --> 14:44.800
It's been dealt with.

14:45.000 --> 14:46.360
I spread some more
ad dollars around

14:46.560 --> 14:47.950
and if any candidate
tries to buy equal time

14:48.150 --> 14:50.680
within a week of Prince, they
won't find any left for sale.

14:50.880 --> 14:51.700
Nicely solved.

14:51.900 --> 14:53.270
Power of
the motherfucking purse.

14:53.470 --> 14:55.390
All over but the shouting.

15:00.900 --> 15:02.440
She's too effective.
We need her out of here.

15:02.640 --> 15:03.990
Isn't she supposed
to be running for Congress,

15:04.190 --> 15:05.720
instead of doing
henchman duty for Prince?

15:05.920 --> 15:09.030
She needs to understand
the hazards of staying.

15:09.990 --> 15:13.660


15:13.860 --> 15:16.330
In my experience,
rich, powerful men

15:16.530 --> 15:18.440
think they want to hear
the unvarnished truth

15:18.640 --> 15:20.060
but don't actually
want to hear it.

15:20.260 --> 15:22.480
Yeah, is this really
just a loyalty test?

15:22.680 --> 15:24.150
If it is, let's pass it,
get back to our desks.

15:24.350 --> 15:25.700
It's earning season, people.

15:25.890 --> 15:27.450
I don't know, best just
call it the way you see it.

15:27.650 --> 15:29.390
You mean as long as
it's what he wants to hear?

15:29.590 --> 15:31.660
I mean, tell him
what he wants to hear

15:31.860 --> 15:32.930
no matter how you see it.

15:33.130 --> 15:34.680
What if that comes across
as inauthentic?

15:34.880 --> 15:36.960
Does your comp
come across as inauthentic?

15:37.160 --> 15:38.480
[Rian]
Guys, easy peasy.

15:38.680 --> 15:41.540
Like seeing your dorm-mate
in an off-off-Broadway play.

15:41.740 --> 15:44.210
You say something vague,
adjective free,

15:44.410 --> 15:45.970
"That was all you up there."

15:46.160 --> 15:48.930
And then let the ego
fill in the blanks.

15:49.130 --> 15:50.510
[chair sliding]

15:50.710 --> 15:52.850
I'm calling bullshit
on this whole exercise,

15:53.050 --> 15:55.890
and I sure as fuck
won't suck up.

15:56.090 --> 15:57.460
[chair rattles]

15:57.660 --> 16:01.610
Mike, you are like
a combination of Benjamin Graham

16:01.810 --> 16:03.920
and fucking Hal
from <i>Space Odyssey, </i>

16:04.120 --> 16:05.460
everywhere, all at once,

16:05.660 --> 16:09.300
processing, prodding me
to make better trades.

16:10.420 --> 16:13.700


16:13.900 --> 16:16.700
Why is there anything you've
been wanting to say to Mike,

16:16.900 --> 16:18.040
but thought you couldn't?

16:18.240 --> 16:19.920
I don't deserve you.

16:20.120 --> 16:22.730
The guilt, it's crushing me.

16:22.930 --> 16:25.800
That's something I think
we should work on.

16:26.000 --> 16:28.510
And the challenges
trading with him, day to day?

16:28.710 --> 16:32.260
I have this recurring dream
in which you make bank.

16:32.460 --> 16:33.660
I'm talking 10X

16:33.860 --> 16:36.970
while doing
an ungodly amount of push ups.

16:37.170 --> 16:38.330
But is it really a dream?

16:38.530 --> 16:41.080


16:41.280 --> 16:43.860
I'm just saying it ain't easy.

16:44.060 --> 16:47.420
When you set a standard that's
through the freaking roof.

16:48.250 --> 16:49.280
[clears throat]

16:49.480 --> 16:50.720
Mike, this is you and me.

16:50.920 --> 16:52.590
Criticism? Who are we kidding?

16:52.790 --> 16:55.680
Uh, would you--
Would you like to, uh...?

17:08.270 --> 17:09.220
[door closes]

17:09.410 --> 17:10.760
- Jesus.
- Let's move on.

17:10.960 --> 17:12.320
Yep.

17:13.990 --> 17:17.660


17:17.860 --> 17:19.200
[elevator dings]

17:25.830 --> 17:28.030
[elevator whirrs]

17:28.230 --> 17:31.110
I love that you're ditching
your race for Congress.

17:31.310 --> 17:33.740
- I am?
- As much as we need you there,

17:33.940 --> 17:34.870
we need you here.

17:35.070 --> 17:36.700
Besides, not enough hand
sanitizer in the world

17:36.900 --> 17:38.100
- to make me do that job.
- [chuckles]

17:38.300 --> 17:41.180
You should go long Purell,
I'm not ditching a thing.

17:41.380 --> 17:43.580
But you're still here?

17:43.780 --> 17:44.900
My filing deadline's
months away.

17:45.100 --> 17:47.820
But we're days away
from Prince's campaign

17:48.020 --> 17:49.190
becoming a black hole.

17:49.390 --> 17:51.760
Everything in its vicinity
sucked right in.

17:51.960 --> 17:54.740
You'll just be part of
the fabric of the thing,

17:54.940 --> 17:57.700
unable to assert yourself
as anything other than

17:57.900 --> 17:59.600
"Prince's fill-in-the-blank".

17:59.800 --> 18:02.160
[chuckles] All because he's
about to throw down a gauntlet?

18:02.360 --> 18:03.520
More of a grenade.

18:03.720 --> 18:05.620
At the parties you'll
need to nominate you.

18:07.250 --> 18:10.780
So I just establish a little
distance when I leave is all.

18:10.980 --> 18:11.970
With your family dough?

18:12.170 --> 18:13.680
With the whitest collar
background

18:13.880 --> 18:15.340
of anyone at the firm?

18:16.050 --> 18:17.990
Ask Chang and Eng.

18:18.190 --> 18:20.850
Not a lot of distance
when you're joined at the hip.

18:21.050 --> 18:22.600
[chuckles]

18:24.520 --> 18:27.430


18:32.650 --> 18:34.340
[Chuck] Must feel different
to walk this hall

18:34.540 --> 18:35.680
as an impresario.

18:35.880 --> 18:37.910
No longer the guy
in the squared circle.

18:38.110 --> 18:39.950
Eh, still feel every bump.

18:40.150 --> 18:42.000
Whether you're giving 'em
whether you're taking 'em,

18:42.200 --> 18:43.790
whether you're scripting 'em.

18:43.990 --> 18:45.850
I've always wondered
if I could do it.

18:46.050 --> 18:47.190
Fall down for a living.

18:47.390 --> 18:50.820
[chuckles] You don't have
that far to fall.

18:51.020 --> 18:52.940
[chuckles]
Look, you could do it.

18:53.140 --> 18:54.950
When this
crowd comes alive,

18:55.150 --> 18:56.180
you'd come alive.

18:56.380 --> 18:58.430
There is nothing else...

18:58.630 --> 19:00.530
- like this.
- [Chuck] Yeah.

19:00.730 --> 19:03.770
Well, no one knows
the game like you do, Hunter.

19:03.970 --> 19:05.660
And that's why
I need your advice.

19:05.860 --> 19:07.350
You got a game that
needs to be played?

19:07.550 --> 19:08.920
Yes, exactly.

19:09.120 --> 19:11.070
I need to turn one guy heel,

19:11.270 --> 19:14.110
and another guy
babyface. In one move.

19:14.310 --> 19:15.090
[Hunter] Oof.

19:15.290 --> 19:17.010
Double turn. Tough to pull off.

19:17.210 --> 19:18.950
But when it's done right,

19:19.150 --> 19:20.870
one of my personal favorites.

19:21.070 --> 19:23.220
How do I pull it off?

19:23.420 --> 19:25.060
You need to let the heel come
in

19:25.260 --> 19:27.000
and get the heat from the
crowd.

19:27.200 --> 19:29.330
Then your babyface comes
and gets the pop.

19:29.530 --> 19:31.250
[soft chuckle]

19:31.450 --> 19:33.190
The heat and the pop, huh?

19:33.390 --> 19:34.550
Oh, yeah.

19:34.750 --> 19:36.990
Tell me more about these guys.
What do you got on 'em?

19:37.190 --> 19:39.550
Well, they both think
they're babyfaces.

19:39.750 --> 19:42.120
That's for damn sure.
But neither one of them is.

19:42.320 --> 19:44.850
Every sitting senator
would give their gavel arm

19:45.050 --> 19:47.290
for a survey result like this.

19:47.490 --> 19:49.400
Did any of it feel real to you?

19:49.600 --> 19:51.110
I can read between the lines.

19:51.310 --> 19:53.230
I picked up that
I can be intimidating.

19:53.430 --> 19:55.360
I'll work on that.

19:59.360 --> 20:00.300
[scoffs]

20:00.500 --> 20:03.640
This is how Vietnams happen.

20:03.840 --> 20:05.520
How politicians lose touch
with reality.

20:05.720 --> 20:07.960
Hard questions stop being asked

20:08.160 --> 20:09.730
and they believe
their own hype.

20:09.930 --> 20:11.360
So you want us to go back
around

20:11.550 --> 20:13.270
and troll for negative
feedback?

20:13.470 --> 20:14.920
So that's written down
somewhere,

20:15.120 --> 20:16.170
so it fucks with Mike's head?

20:16.370 --> 20:17.440
[Wendy]
I wouldn't frame it like that.

20:17.640 --> 20:19.360
But if he's going to ask
the rest of us,

20:19.560 --> 20:20.950
the country, to take inventory,

20:21.150 --> 20:23.450
then he should
really fucking do it.

20:23.650 --> 20:24.830
Otherwise, he's as fake

20:25.030 --> 20:26.180
as the politicians
he's running against,

20:26.380 --> 20:27.560
and the voters are going
to smell it on him

20:27.760 --> 20:29.560
and send him packing.

20:31.600 --> 20:32.980
She's right.

20:34.230 --> 20:37.800
You want a samurai sword
and Hattori Hanz blade?

20:38.000 --> 20:40.340
Those only come
from the hottest flames.

20:40.540 --> 20:44.820
Find me a master swordsmith
without some serious burns.

20:47.200 --> 20:49.530


20:55.750 --> 20:57.000
[Wags] He's letting you

20:57.210 --> 20:58.400
run a second round
of honesty sessions?

20:58.600 --> 21:00.750
[Wendy] Without Prince
in the room this time.

21:01.420 --> 21:02.510
No Luke either.

21:02.710 --> 21:04.050
I'm not comfortable with this.

21:04.250 --> 21:05.870
We don't know where
actual honesty will lead.

21:06.070 --> 21:07.140
[Wags]
Fuck yeah, we do.

21:07.340 --> 21:08.540
The greatest
televised meltdown

21:08.740 --> 21:10.020
since Howard Beale.

21:10.220 --> 21:12.210
Prince's narcissism
is a mile-wide

21:12.410 --> 21:13.440
and a micron thick.

21:13.640 --> 21:15.880
Watch the movie.
Beale stays on air,

21:16.080 --> 21:17.340
Schumacher gets
kicked to the curb.

21:17.540 --> 21:19.260
I want to keep having
a firm to run.

21:19.460 --> 21:20.340
Watch it to the end.

21:20.540 --> 21:21.900
Beale gets his brains blown
out.

21:22.110 --> 21:23.390
Schumacher gets
to schtup a young,

21:23.590 --> 21:25.100
luscious-as-a-plum
Faye Dunaway.

21:25.300 --> 21:27.140
[Wendy]
Taylor isn't wrong.

21:27.340 --> 21:28.850
This could implode MPC,

21:29.050 --> 21:32.370
as well as the campaign
and all of our places in it.

21:37.040 --> 21:40.840
I wanna slam Prince's ego
with a battering ram.

21:42.630 --> 21:45.340
No telling where
the fragments will land.

21:46.720 --> 21:48.910
If it hurts business.

21:49.110 --> 21:51.010
If it blows us up, too...

21:52.310 --> 21:54.020
price we gotta pay.

22:09.700 --> 22:10.890
[sighs]

22:11.090 --> 22:13.310
One question, related
to the files we discussed

22:13.510 --> 22:14.950
a few weeks back.

22:15.830 --> 22:17.610
Yep.

22:17.810 --> 22:19.190
If I stay on board here,
am I killing

22:19.390 --> 22:20.880
my chances
with the mainstream party?

22:21.080 --> 22:22.880
Can't expect either party
to bear hug you

22:23.080 --> 22:24.530
after he shoots 'em
in the vitals.

22:24.730 --> 22:27.200
What if I wall myself off
from the campaign?

22:27.400 --> 22:29.370
Restrict myself to firm
business until I leave?

22:29.570 --> 22:32.040
The firm is the campaign.

22:32.240 --> 22:33.230
No wall to be built

22:33.430 --> 22:35.580
unless you wanna drywall
your own office door.

22:35.780 --> 22:36.850
[exhales]

22:37.050 --> 22:39.480
I was hoping we could,
uh, I don't know...

22:40.100 --> 22:41.150
think outside the box.

22:41.350 --> 22:43.720
Mmm, not so easy
when you're in one.

22:43.920 --> 22:45.780
[sighs]

22:46.820 --> 22:48.240
Got the case for ya.

22:48.440 --> 22:49.430
Commodities fraud.

22:49.630 --> 22:51.720
Uh, market manipulation
in the oil industry.

22:51.920 --> 22:53.100
That'll do. [sighs]

22:53.300 --> 22:54.960
Sure you want
to go down this road?

22:55.160 --> 22:57.330
We list Andolov
as an expert witness,

22:57.530 --> 22:59.360
then asked DOJ and DHS

22:59.560 --> 23:01.090
to parole him
into the country.

23:01.290 --> 23:03.070
Get ready for
some hairpin turns.

23:03.270 --> 23:06.490
The guy's a sanctioned oligarch
who you chased out.

23:06.690 --> 23:07.990
I mean, there's impossible,

23:08.190 --> 23:09.950
then there's climbing
the Dawn Wall

23:10.150 --> 23:12.390
with a pair of Havaianas
and a bag of chalk.

23:12.590 --> 23:14.230
I think I can sell it.

23:14.430 --> 23:16.540
I also learned that
Grigor's wife is not alone

23:16.740 --> 23:18.960
in her divorce action--
she's got a backer,

23:19.160 --> 23:20.900
a hedge fund,
he's bankrolling her,

23:21.100 --> 23:22.250
no doubt for a big piece
of the settlement.

23:22.450 --> 23:25.820
- Who?
- Our very own Todd Krakow.

23:26.980 --> 23:28.680
And knowing him,
that's not the only reason

23:28.880 --> 23:30.030
he's lurking around.

23:30.230 --> 23:31.450
[chuckles] Because
what we need here

23:31.650 --> 23:32.680
are some more obstacles.

23:32.880 --> 23:34.780
[sighs]

23:36.080 --> 23:38.120
Damn the torpedoes,
file the parole request.

23:38.320 --> 23:39.690
[Ira] I've got
something else for you.

23:39.890 --> 23:41.170
- Can it wait till morning?
- Uh...

23:41.370 --> 23:43.090
you're going to want
to see this today.

23:43.290 --> 23:44.750
[Chuck sighs]

23:47.590 --> 23:49.840


23:51.590 --> 23:52.700
Dad.

23:52.900 --> 23:56.350
Uh, your pal Bunky
signed a consent form.

23:56.550 --> 23:58.670
Well, hold the fucking roll.
If your boy signed off on it,

23:58.870 --> 24:00.230
how come he didn't
get the missus

24:00.430 --> 24:01.610
to do the extraction pre-mortem?

24:01.810 --> 24:02.960
I mean, that's lots more fun.

24:03.160 --> 24:04.230
You know what I'm sayin',
baby girl?

24:04.430 --> 24:05.550
He didn't want to raise a kid.

24:05.750 --> 24:07.970
He wanted a posthumous tot
to live on after him.

24:08.170 --> 24:10.050
That's like that fucking movie
about the octopus.

24:10.250 --> 24:11.490
She popped some eggs
from her cooch,

24:11.690 --> 24:14.160
and then she slides
into an undersea death spiral.

24:15.030 --> 24:17.160
Hm.

24:17.360 --> 24:20.700
This isn't about Bunky at all.
What is it?

24:22.620 --> 24:24.420
Okay, fine.

24:24.620 --> 24:26.000
I'll tell you.

24:28.460 --> 24:31.010
It's Roxanne and Willow.

24:32.420 --> 24:34.030
[indistinct chatter]

24:34.230 --> 24:36.800
[Chuck Sr.]
<i>I saw them praying... </i>

24:37.550 --> 24:39.350
<i>to Jesus. </i>

24:39.550 --> 24:41.520
When we agreed
we wouldn't raise Willow

24:41.720 --> 24:43.730
with religion at all.

24:45.810 --> 24:48.720
Beware, Sonny Boy,
legacy is a lie!

24:48.920 --> 24:52.180
There is no control
in the hereafter.

24:52.380 --> 24:53.600
Oh, shit. It's true.

24:53.800 --> 24:55.410
You know, once they get
the Jesus fever,

24:55.610 --> 24:56.640
it's rarely treatable.

24:56.840 --> 24:58.520
Just like the fucking
Orthodox in my tribe.

24:58.720 --> 25:01.580
Yeah, a Rhoades
spouting the Lord's Prayer,

25:01.780 --> 25:04.440
I know what a disaster
that is for you.

25:04.640 --> 25:06.050
You need to talk to Roxanne.

25:06.250 --> 25:08.050
Just rein it in
before it takes root.

25:08.250 --> 25:11.090
Not in a talking mood.

25:13.380 --> 25:14.490
I'm drawing up my demands

25:14.690 --> 25:17.120
for the upbringing
of my progeny.

25:17.320 --> 25:21.100
Schooling, vacations,
earthly pursuits.

25:21.300 --> 25:23.520
This-- This God shit?

25:23.720 --> 25:25.020
Strictly off the list.

25:25.220 --> 25:27.550
Because ultimatums
work so well in a marriage?

25:27.750 --> 25:31.690
If she won't heed mine,
then we are headed for divorce.

25:32.440 --> 25:34.280
And I'm going for custody.

25:34.480 --> 25:37.200


25:39.910 --> 25:41.950
[door slides shut]

25:52.170 --> 25:56.120
I knew you'd come.
I've been expecting you.

25:56.320 --> 25:59.290
I saw in the papers
you're back in your old job.

25:59.490 --> 26:00.580
Indeed.

26:00.780 --> 26:03.330
But I figured
you'd make an appointment.

26:03.530 --> 26:06.770
I'm not actually here for that.

26:08.020 --> 26:09.780
It's about my father.

26:09.980 --> 26:12.650
Oh. Well. Usually is.

26:12.850 --> 26:16.570
[Chuck scoffs]
No, I need some information.

26:18.320 --> 26:20.660
About the nature of control.

26:20.860 --> 26:22.430
Dominance.

26:22.630 --> 26:26.150
Why some seem
unable to give it up.

26:26.350 --> 26:28.250
You trying to save yourself?

26:28.450 --> 26:30.380
[Chuck]
No. Not this time, no.

26:30.580 --> 26:33.040
My dad needs some peace.

26:34.090 --> 26:36.620
But his daughter...

26:36.810 --> 26:41.220
she needs to be spared
the kind of upbringing I had.

26:42.260 --> 26:44.690
That relentless,
controlling instinct which--

26:44.890 --> 26:46.670
Which led you here
in the first place.

26:46.870 --> 26:51.420
Which led me to mirror him
in 98% of my interactions.

26:51.620 --> 26:55.230
And then to have to completely
repudiate it here.

26:56.820 --> 26:58.320
Sometimes there's
a certain comfort

26:58.520 --> 27:01.330
in jumping
at others' command.

27:01.530 --> 27:03.680
Control is all
an illusion anyway.

27:03.880 --> 27:05.350
Huh. Tell that to the guy

27:05.550 --> 27:07.710
in the business end
of the truncheon.

27:07.910 --> 27:11.210
But if you're
paying someone to wield it,

27:11.960 --> 27:14.000
who's really in control?

27:15.460 --> 27:19.350
End of the day,
client gets the meal.

27:19.550 --> 27:22.310
I just plate the food.

27:22.510 --> 27:25.040
You think my dad
is fooling himself?

27:25.240 --> 27:27.770
[Troy] Raging against
his own impotence, maybe.

27:27.970 --> 27:30.310
His mortality.

27:30.510 --> 27:33.130
Control is often
an expression of fear.

27:33.330 --> 27:35.650
People who truly believe
they're in control?

27:35.850 --> 27:39.910
More likely to escalate
their actions till they fail.

27:40.110 --> 27:41.950
Leads to poor decision making.

27:42.150 --> 27:44.370
- Magical thinking.
- Hm.

27:45.410 --> 27:46.640
Problem is...

27:46.840 --> 27:49.950
telling a controller
not to doesn't work.

27:50.750 --> 27:51.690
I've noticed.

27:51.890 --> 27:53.480
Your hope lies in convincing
him

27:53.680 --> 27:56.550
that his true power
is best displayed

27:56.750 --> 27:59.170
in not having to use it.

28:00.090 --> 28:02.590


28:07.720 --> 28:09.350
I promised them anonymity.

28:09.550 --> 28:11.920
Then work to get them past
their instinct for flattery,

28:12.120 --> 28:13.750
for base self-interest.

28:13.950 --> 28:16.190
I'm ready for
the unplugged version.

28:17.400 --> 28:20.760
"Self-satisfied."
"Loves himself."

28:20.960 --> 28:23.200
"Mother Teresa of Wall Street."

28:24.360 --> 28:25.700
"Loves the smell
of his own farts,

28:25.900 --> 28:28.810
like the "Smug Alert"
episode of <i>South Park"? </i>

28:29.010 --> 28:30.560
- Never saw that one.
- I have.

28:30.760 --> 28:32.790
It's a top-tier episode.
Heh. Who said that?

28:32.990 --> 28:34.520
You can't think
I'm gonna name names.

28:34.720 --> 28:36.860
I just-- I want to do
some relationship repair.

28:37.060 --> 28:38.700
[stammers]
Of course, no.

28:38.900 --> 28:42.180
Uh, "Entitled, thinks he can
buy us off with private planes.

28:42.380 --> 28:45.180
I mean, I'll take the flights,
but fuck that."

28:45.890 --> 28:47.580
[sighs then scoffs]

28:47.780 --> 28:50.580
"Forces you to come to his party
and act like you like it

28:50.780 --> 28:52.380
while he slakes his appetite--"

28:52.580 --> 28:53.480
[Luke]
Stop right there.

28:53.680 --> 28:54.730
There's no reason for Mike

28:54.930 --> 28:57.380
to be subject to
the petty staff jealousies

28:57.580 --> 28:59.190
and--and character sniping.

28:59.400 --> 29:01.200
I mean, we all
sat through your round.

29:01.400 --> 29:02.840
I didn't take you
for the squeamish type.

29:03.040 --> 29:04.970
And this is when
we bring it back around,

29:05.170 --> 29:07.040
put it in a context?

29:07.240 --> 29:08.830
[scoffs]

29:09.030 --> 29:10.910
Here's the context.
You have to decide

29:11.120 --> 29:12.730
what taking inventory
actually means.

29:12.930 --> 29:14.540
Whether you can push through
the friction

29:14.740 --> 29:16.670
as commander in chief,
a lot fucking worse

29:16.870 --> 29:18.030
than what you heard just now.

29:18.230 --> 29:19.440
And do what must be done.

29:19.640 --> 29:20.970
What only you can do
for the country.

29:21.170 --> 29:24.410
Even if it turns you
into a dartboard.

29:24.610 --> 29:27.160
I think you can,
or I'd be lying to your face

29:27.360 --> 29:30.560
like everyone else on that floor
instead of, you know...

29:30.760 --> 29:32.810
giving you what you asked for.

29:34.890 --> 29:36.900


29:40.650 --> 29:42.320
That'll be all.

29:51.660 --> 29:53.330
[door closes]

30:01.090 --> 30:03.170
[clears throat]

30:07.930 --> 30:10.640
These are all A-list attorneys.

30:10.840 --> 30:11.980
Serious political chops, too.

30:12.180 --> 30:13.750
You think
we need more firepower?

30:13.950 --> 30:14.960
[Sacker] No.

30:15.160 --> 30:18.800
But I don't want to leave
without replacing myself.

30:19.000 --> 30:21.900
But it's time. Past time.

30:22.980 --> 30:24.360
The speech is tomorrow.

30:24.560 --> 30:27.430
I need to get with the party
that can nominate me.

30:27.630 --> 30:29.810
Terms of my hire, remember?

30:30.010 --> 30:31.490
What do you want?

30:32.200 --> 30:33.410
What will it take

30:33.610 --> 30:36.440
to stick around longer
till we can right the ship?

30:36.640 --> 30:38.380
If I stay
and help you right it,

30:38.580 --> 30:41.530
it'll be pretty hard
to get off it.

30:41.730 --> 30:43.610
If your departure
is made public,

30:43.810 --> 30:44.880
this of all weeks...

30:45.080 --> 30:46.140
Maybe we all go quiet on this

30:46.340 --> 30:47.590
until the hand-off's complete.

30:47.800 --> 30:50.220
It has to be public.
It has to be now.

30:50.840 --> 30:52.020
A couple of days at the most.

30:52.220 --> 30:55.940
I need to establish
a little distance to him.

30:56.140 --> 30:58.900
Scrub your name off mine
while I still can.

30:59.100 --> 31:01.350
- It's just politics, Mike.
- [sighs]

31:02.730 --> 31:04.360
I hope you understand.

31:08.780 --> 31:10.740
Don't walk away
from Prince Capital

31:10.940 --> 31:12.060
or Prince himself.

31:12.260 --> 31:13.390
I don't quit now,

31:13.590 --> 31:15.370
both parties will freeze me
out.

31:15.570 --> 31:16.900
Nothing on the plus side
of the ledger

31:17.090 --> 31:18.870
competes with that.

31:19.660 --> 31:21.580
"Love To Love You, Baby."

31:23.250 --> 31:24.570
Come again?

31:24.770 --> 31:27.280
It's the song that took
dance music from the club floor

31:27.480 --> 31:28.820
to the top of the charts.

31:29.020 --> 31:30.510
Broke me as a music manager.

31:30.710 --> 31:34.060
Made Donna Summer into
the queen of a whole new genre.

31:34.260 --> 31:36.120
You said it ended badly.

31:36.320 --> 31:37.540
Always does.

31:37.740 --> 31:41.860
But before that, she was
my double platinum ticket.

31:42.060 --> 31:43.630
No bigger pop star
in the '70s.

31:43.830 --> 31:47.570
No Black woman, beside Diana
with her cultural power,

31:47.770 --> 31:49.360
her crossover cachet.

31:49.570 --> 31:51.100
And she knew it.

31:51.300 --> 31:53.010
Came to me to cut my
percentage.

31:53.210 --> 31:55.620
Once, then again and again.

31:55.820 --> 31:57.830
Natural progression
with most stars.

31:58.030 --> 32:01.730
But I hung in,
choked down every indignity.

32:01.930 --> 32:03.670
And do you know why?

32:03.870 --> 32:05.490
Because everyone
answered my call.

32:05.690 --> 32:07.510
Just hoping it'd be about
Donna.

32:07.710 --> 32:09.780
It would've been worth it
to do the job for free

32:09.980 --> 32:11.950
for that alone.

32:12.150 --> 32:13.760
No indignities
at Prince Capital.

32:13.960 --> 32:16.080
But unlike Donna,
the name is about to be

32:16.280 --> 32:17.830
a liability for me.

32:18.030 --> 32:20.170
You don't want to be frozen
out.

32:20.370 --> 32:21.710
I get it.

32:21.910 --> 32:24.590
But how cold are you going
to feel in the wilderness?

32:24.790 --> 32:29.150
In the dead of winter?
When your calls go unanswered?

32:29.900 --> 32:31.990


32:37.080 --> 32:39.960
Surprise, surprise.
We've got a Russia problem.

32:40.160 --> 32:41.000
Hmm. Oh!

32:41.200 --> 32:44.270
[Chuck] Apparently,
it's going around.

32:44.470 --> 32:46.760
Chuck. My friends in DC

32:46.960 --> 32:48.950
tell me you're trying
to bring Grigor Andolov

32:49.150 --> 32:51.010
in as some bullshit witness.

32:51.210 --> 32:52.550
Are you fucking crazy?

32:52.750 --> 32:55.080
How's the country better off
with that droog in it?

32:55.280 --> 32:56.910
Uh, let's reframe that.

32:57.110 --> 33:00.040
How many tens of millions of
dollars do you stand to lose

33:00.240 --> 33:01.880
if he can contest
his divorce action?

33:02.070 --> 33:04.500
Mm. You should know better
than to mock the crime

33:04.700 --> 33:06.090
- of spousal abandonment.
- [chuckles]

33:06.290 --> 33:07.550
Or the stigma and isolation?

33:07.750 --> 33:09.420
The inability
to plan one's future?

33:09.620 --> 33:11.950
A woman's emotions
torn fucking asunder.

33:12.150 --> 33:13.120
[Chuck] Ohh...

33:13.320 --> 33:14.970
You're not just
bankrolling her.

33:15.170 --> 33:17.240
You're sleeping with her.

33:18.070 --> 33:19.730
- [Krakow] Okay, look...
- [chuckles]

33:19.930 --> 33:22.190
[Krakow]
It started off all business,

33:22.390 --> 33:24.520
but Oksana is
a very soulful woman.

33:24.720 --> 33:26.710
She's been through a lot.
[inhales]

33:26.910 --> 33:28.210
The heart wants
what the heart wants.

33:28.410 --> 33:31.200
So does the DOJ,
and we need the guy here.

33:31.400 --> 33:33.030
Then I may need
to align with forces

33:33.230 --> 33:34.990
whose interests run
counter to yours.

33:35.190 --> 33:37.180
- In a big fucking way.
- [Chuck snickers]

33:37.380 --> 33:40.510
And I never do my enemies
minor boo-boos, Chuck.

33:44.730 --> 33:47.880
Keep up that watered-down
Machiavelli shit with me,

33:48.080 --> 33:50.190
the feds will be
a far more pressing problem

33:50.390 --> 33:52.450
than some foreign actor.

33:52.650 --> 33:54.800
You better not mess
with that divorce proceeding.

33:55.000 --> 33:57.240
Oh, that one's all yours.

33:57.440 --> 33:58.990
[scoffs]

33:59.190 --> 34:01.230
[Chuck snickers]

34:01.430 --> 34:02.810
[Ira]
He's not the only grouser.

34:03.010 --> 34:04.400
I just heard from DeGiulio.

34:04.600 --> 34:06.960
He got the request to parole
Grigor back into the States?

34:07.160 --> 34:08.610
Wants to discuss it in person.

34:08.810 --> 34:10.820
Along with your old pals
Governor Sweeney

34:11.020 --> 34:12.610
and Attorney General Mahar.

34:12.810 --> 34:13.860
The three of them together.

34:14.060 --> 34:15.660
[Ira] When they come at you
as a three man,

34:15.860 --> 34:17.930
think chair shot,
not rubber stamp.

34:18.130 --> 34:20.620
My ink pad's at the ready.

34:20.820 --> 34:24.690
Chuck, is it really worth
choosing Grigor over Krakow

34:24.890 --> 34:26.960
and not one,
but two levels of government?

34:27.160 --> 34:28.320
To please this guy
of all people.

34:28.520 --> 34:29.840
I mean, what's he ever
done for you...

34:30.040 --> 34:30.900
Hm.

34:31.100 --> 34:32.820
...except wear you out
and haunt your days?

34:33.020 --> 34:36.800
No, this is
the vaunted Bobby Axelrod,

34:37.000 --> 34:38.970
mover of markets,

34:39.170 --> 34:41.700
puller of levers.

34:41.900 --> 34:45.080
And he needed me.
[scoffs]

34:45.280 --> 34:49.150
Called me. Had to ask me
for a personal favor.

34:49.350 --> 34:52.090
Offered to be in my debt.

34:54.000 --> 34:58.050
Sure, I wanted to say no,
almost did. But...

34:58.250 --> 34:59.990
Well, that's too rare
and valuable

35:00.190 --> 35:02.140
a commodity these days.

35:03.430 --> 35:06.470
Especially from one
who knows what it means.

35:07.770 --> 35:10.650
Well, that is more old school
than Sammy Davis Jr.

35:10.850 --> 35:12.690
tapping with
the Will Mastin Trio.

35:12.890 --> 35:15.110


35:23.530 --> 35:24.850
I lead from the front.

35:25.050 --> 35:26.980
I do everything I ask
of those under my command

35:27.180 --> 35:28.670
and not from
a goddamn swivel chair.

35:28.870 --> 35:31.230
The difference between you
and General Patton?

35:31.430 --> 35:33.650
He didn't ask for
his employee's criticism.

35:33.850 --> 35:35.090
He just slapped them
in the face.

35:35.290 --> 35:36.780
Criticism informs, elucidates.

35:36.980 --> 35:38.510
This was insubordination.

35:39.420 --> 35:41.280
Maybe Luke was right--
maybe you weren't ready

35:41.480 --> 35:43.120
for the full fire hose.

35:43.320 --> 35:46.520
My own people think
that they can lie to me,

35:46.720 --> 35:48.220
mock me.

35:49.520 --> 35:50.900
Plus, Sacker's leaving,

35:51.100 --> 35:52.480
planning on
"distancing herself"?

35:52.680 --> 35:53.880
We were cruising along

35:54.080 --> 35:55.360
at flank speed before all this.

35:55.560 --> 35:57.320
Mm. The presidential.

35:57.520 --> 35:59.430
When did I become Lex Luthor?

35:59.630 --> 36:01.010
Anytime somebody
runs for office,

36:01.210 --> 36:03.450
they either become Superman
or that other thing.

36:03.650 --> 36:04.830
I didn't change.

36:05.030 --> 36:06.660
Everybody looks at you
through different eyes now,

36:06.860 --> 36:09.810
but that doesn't matter.
What matters is this:

36:10.010 --> 36:12.070
There's nothing wrong
with deciding you want

36:12.260 --> 36:13.940
the unvarnished,
unquestioned love.

36:14.140 --> 36:17.840
In fact, that may be
the most healthy choice.

36:22.220 --> 36:24.720
Sometimes quitting
isn't capitulation.

36:26.350 --> 36:29.940
Sometimes it shows grit
and wisdom.

36:30.140 --> 36:32.440


36:35.520 --> 36:38.360


36:50.620 --> 36:52.210
[net swishes]

37:17.230 --> 37:18.130
Scooter called you?

37:18.330 --> 37:19.740
[Andy]
He told me what happened.

37:19.940 --> 37:22.090
I know this is
where you'd go.

37:22.290 --> 37:23.370
Well, it used to actually work.

37:23.570 --> 37:24.930
Now I feel the chill
in this room, too.

37:25.130 --> 37:27.040
Well, too warm
and you slip on the court.

37:27.240 --> 37:28.530
[scoffs]

37:31.040 --> 37:34.420
I used to feel the warmth
in every room I entered.

37:34.620 --> 37:36.040
Especially
Michael Prince Capital.

37:36.240 --> 37:37.400
Now it just seems like a lie.

37:37.600 --> 37:40.540
Those rooms were warm
because you paid them.

37:41.210 --> 37:43.220
I told myself I didn't care.

37:43.420 --> 37:46.160
But I thought the warmth
was real. Or I wanted to.

37:46.360 --> 37:47.810
[Andy] Then let's
talk court conditions.

37:48.010 --> 37:51.430
[sighs]
I was at Indiana A&M, too.

37:52.350 --> 37:53.460
My teammates loved me there.

37:53.660 --> 37:55.060
If we're really
taking inventory,

37:55.260 --> 37:56.460
some of them hated your guts.

37:56.660 --> 37:58.960
Until they got to know me,
maybe.

37:59.160 --> 37:59.940
No.

38:00.140 --> 38:02.300
Until you lead them
to some wins.

38:02.500 --> 38:04.440
Then they loved you.

38:07.360 --> 38:09.470
I just had to show them
I was all about the team.

38:09.670 --> 38:12.410
The team was all about you.
Always.

38:12.610 --> 38:13.940
You always had the ball.

38:14.140 --> 38:15.900
You always made your shots
or dished it.

38:16.100 --> 38:18.630
They had to learn that
the path to glory

38:18.830 --> 38:20.990
ran through you.

38:21.190 --> 38:24.200
So I shouldn't worry about
seeking real love?

38:24.400 --> 38:28.100
I'm saying, the way to get it
is to be a winner.

38:28.300 --> 38:30.100
That's as real
as it fucking gets.

38:30.300 --> 38:33.520
Is that cold or superficial
or hollow?

38:33.720 --> 38:37.150
Well, that's the world
we're living in.

38:37.350 --> 38:39.980
And it's the one
you say you want to lead.

38:40.180 --> 38:42.440


38:48.150 --> 38:50.160
[indistinct chatter]

38:50.360 --> 38:51.910
And he's fucking late.

38:53.410 --> 38:56.290
Quite the assemblage
for a pro forma parole request.

38:56.490 --> 38:58.980
Pro fucking forma?
Coddling a Russian criminal

38:59.180 --> 39:00.420
on the dawn of
a second Cold War.

39:00.620 --> 39:03.400
Last I saw you, Governor,
you were forcing me from office

39:03.600 --> 39:04.780
in a bloodless coup.

39:04.980 --> 39:06.590
I'd say cold wars
are your <i>métier. </i>

39:06.790 --> 39:08.780
Uh, Mr. Andolov has agreed

39:08.980 --> 39:10.850
to cooperate
in a critical case.

39:11.050 --> 39:13.060
His safe passage
will be strictly limited--

39:13.260 --> 39:15.810
To rat-fucking me and my
biggest donor, Todd Krakow.

39:16.010 --> 39:18.440
[Daevisha] Chuck,
my office, your old office,

39:18.640 --> 39:21.270
you personally ran Grigor
out of this country.

39:21.480 --> 39:24.510
Surely, whatever grudge you hold
against the governor--

39:24.710 --> 39:27.260
Me? I'm all about
moving forward.

39:27.460 --> 39:29.070
This has to stop
at the water's edge.

39:29.270 --> 39:31.080
Let this fucker in and we're
going to look ridiculous.

39:31.280 --> 39:32.470
Like patsies. Like...

39:32.670 --> 39:34.540
Putin's got pee tapes
on the lot of us.

39:34.740 --> 39:37.520
I know better
than to try to stop you, Chuck.

39:37.720 --> 39:38.980
You will find a way over,

39:39.180 --> 39:40.210
you will find a way through.

39:40.410 --> 39:42.550
Used to be my <i>modus,</i> sure.

39:42.750 --> 39:44.710
I am appealing
to you, though.

39:44.920 --> 39:46.170
Don't alienate us.

39:46.370 --> 39:47.880
And don't burn Todd Krakow

39:48.080 --> 39:49.640
and 50 other
political powerhouses

39:49.840 --> 39:51.470
in your first months back
at Southern.

39:51.670 --> 39:54.450
Don't make them your last.

39:54.650 --> 39:57.290
I used to believe in
zero-sum...

39:57.490 --> 39:59.980
in choosing a side,
generally my own,

40:00.180 --> 40:01.540
and alienating all others.

40:01.740 --> 40:07.050
But this go-around, I see
that we can all be winners,

40:07.250 --> 40:08.990
all be friends.

40:09.190 --> 40:11.100
Why draw lines in the sand

40:11.300 --> 40:12.910
when we can build a castle?

40:13.110 --> 40:15.200
[scoffs]
Castles made of sand?

40:15.400 --> 40:18.770
You know, it's happened, Chuck.
You've lost your fucking mind.

40:18.970 --> 40:20.210
Maybe I just found it, Bob.

40:20.410 --> 40:23.420
Chuck,
in a known language, please.

40:24.330 --> 40:28.030
I'm talking about
telling our own story.

40:28.230 --> 40:31.120
A story in which we work
the emotional levers

40:31.320 --> 40:33.370
to all get
what we actually want.

40:33.570 --> 40:37.180
And how exactly do we reach
this promised land?

40:37.380 --> 40:42.230
My special advisor on this
will answer all your questions.

40:42.430 --> 40:45.600
You might say
he does it for a living.

40:46.520 --> 40:48.450
<i> Time to play the game  </i>

40:48.650 --> 40:51.820
[heavy metal music
playing over phone speaker]

40:53.400 --> 40:56.530
[crowd cheering
over phone speaker]

40:58.700 --> 41:00.790
[singer cackles]

41:01.540 --> 41:03.110
[music ends]

41:03.310 --> 41:05.920
So, you found
a good lawyer yet?

41:06.670 --> 41:07.590
Excuse me?

41:07.790 --> 41:09.400
[Chuck]
Your custody case.

41:09.600 --> 41:12.320
Oh, I know your prenup's
a fortress of steel,

41:12.520 --> 41:15.470
and that you're ready to crush.

41:16.300 --> 41:17.430
I'm short-listing litigators

41:17.630 --> 41:20.160
and still building out
my list of demands.

41:20.360 --> 41:21.810
Uh-huh.

41:22.480 --> 41:24.190
[Chuck Sr.]
Go ahead, son.

41:24.390 --> 41:25.710
I've known you
long enough to know

41:25.910 --> 41:27.360
when you've got a point to
make.

41:27.560 --> 41:28.570
[chuckles]
Well...

41:28.770 --> 41:30.630
probably not one
that's welcome here, so--

41:30.830 --> 41:32.610
Out with it.

41:34.070 --> 41:38.720
No, it's just that I've noticed
that power is the ability

41:38.920 --> 41:40.690
to influence others,

41:40.880 --> 41:43.230
not dictate to them.

41:43.430 --> 41:47.750
True power is
not having to use it.

41:50.250 --> 41:53.070
Are you gonna flash
your history chops now

41:53.270 --> 41:56.240
and hold forth
on how the great emperors

41:56.440 --> 41:58.890
and cons were such
because they showed mercy?

41:59.090 --> 42:00.120
I'm not.

42:00.320 --> 42:02.420
We both know I'm talking
about your daughter.

42:02.610 --> 42:03.600
[Chuck Sr.] That's right.

42:03.800 --> 42:05.770
Now, she ought not be beholden

42:05.970 --> 42:07.400
to some made-up deity.

42:07.600 --> 42:11.110
When you'd rather have her
be beholden to you.

42:12.860 --> 42:14.550
Your way.

42:14.750 --> 42:16.100
You'll have her obedience

42:16.300 --> 42:19.640
and you'll have moments
of her affection...

42:19.840 --> 42:21.520
Uh, she's human, after all.

42:21.720 --> 42:26.230
And won't be able to escape
her inclination to love you,

42:26.430 --> 42:29.040
but she'll try.

42:30.250 --> 42:32.530
Oh, boy, how she'll try,

42:32.730 --> 42:36.170
if you run power games
on her and her mother.

42:38.470 --> 42:40.500
Domination...

42:40.690 --> 42:43.370
is an all-or-nothing
proposition.

42:43.570 --> 42:47.440
It does not work
if you carve out exemptions.

42:47.640 --> 42:49.460
What is it that
you're suggesting?

42:49.660 --> 42:53.110
Go on dominating
everyone else in your life.

42:53.900 --> 42:56.820
Put your stamp on things
and mark your turf.

42:57.020 --> 42:59.620
Yes, and go ahead
and show her that,

42:59.820 --> 43:01.680
when she's old enough
to apprehend it.

43:01.880 --> 43:05.160
But when it comes to her now...

43:06.290 --> 43:08.540
give her a sense of
stability...

43:09.040 --> 43:10.710
and self worth.

43:10.910 --> 43:15.670
Because that's where
<i>true</i> power comes from.

43:20.470 --> 43:22.370
Ease up.

43:22.570 --> 43:24.310
As a means of achieving
the same result.

43:24.510 --> 43:29.850
Actually, control them more
by seeming to cede it.

43:31.520 --> 43:33.150
Wouldn't have worked with you.

43:34.020 --> 43:35.300
Who's to say

43:35.500 --> 43:37.740
I may have needed the firm
hand,

43:37.940 --> 43:39.930
but neither of these
women are me.

43:40.130 --> 43:41.370
Oh, that's for damn sure.

43:41.570 --> 43:43.520
[Chuck] It could spare
you a custody fight.

43:43.720 --> 43:46.660
You might even get
what's on that list of yours,

43:46.870 --> 43:48.150
and they'll never know

43:48.350 --> 43:51.620
they played right
into what you wanted.

43:58.010 --> 43:59.490
I like this plan.

43:59.690 --> 44:00.450
Hm.

44:00.650 --> 44:01.580
Some sense must have been

44:01.780 --> 44:03.490
whipped into you after all.

44:03.690 --> 44:06.100
That firm hand. Yep.

44:08.390 --> 44:10.600
Okay, sonny...

44:11.020 --> 44:12.440
I will try it your way.

44:12.640 --> 44:14.150
[Chuck] Good.

44:15.060 --> 44:16.220
[Chuck clears throat]

44:16.420 --> 44:17.740
Continental style in this
house,

44:17.940 --> 44:20.200
left hand, tines downward.

44:20.400 --> 44:23.320
This look like
Ruby fucking Tuesday to you?

44:26.580 --> 44:28.950


44:35.130 --> 44:36.510
[Luke] Speech of his life.

44:36.710 --> 44:38.280
I cannot believe
he missed the run-through.

44:38.480 --> 44:39.820
[Scooter] Mike doesn't
need run-throughs.

44:40.020 --> 44:41.570
He's Africa/Brass-era Coltrane.

44:41.770 --> 44:44.240
- He finds it as he goes.
- Can you find it if it went?

44:44.440 --> 44:46.450
We're live on eight channels
in five minutes

44:46.650 --> 44:48.100
and he's not even here.

44:48.720 --> 44:49.940
[Bradford Luke]
There he is.

44:50.140 --> 44:53.060
[Prince] Who's ready
to turn this upside down?

44:53.260 --> 44:54.550
Didn't need a run-through.

44:54.750 --> 44:56.940
Any more than Jay-Z
needs to write down his lyrics.

44:57.140 --> 44:59.150
Just roll tape and let me go.

44:59.980 --> 45:02.780


45:03.740 --> 45:05.290
Thank you.

45:05.490 --> 45:07.620
For not keeping me safe.

45:07.820 --> 45:08.770
In my bubble.

45:08.970 --> 45:10.710
The idea that I would
reassess my campaign,

45:10.910 --> 45:13.360
quit, because of a few grumblers
in the company...

45:13.560 --> 45:15.900
Well, I needed to hear that.

45:16.100 --> 45:19.470
I was a professional
boot in the ass.

45:19.670 --> 45:21.920
Finally saw what you were doing.

45:22.550 --> 45:25.870
The destiny, it's in me.

45:26.070 --> 45:29.100
I knew you'd put yourself
back together.

45:29.300 --> 45:30.720
Glad you did.

45:31.270 --> 45:32.980
[woman] Ready?

45:33.180 --> 45:34.940


45:37.650 --> 45:38.740
I put him back together

45:38.940 --> 45:42.190
after you kicked the pieces
across the floor.

45:44.240 --> 45:46.450
[footsteps receding]

45:56.580 --> 45:58.230
I thought you were out the
door.

45:58.430 --> 46:01.740
I'd like to stay at MPC
until my filing deadline.

46:01.940 --> 46:04.590
Then run as an independent
on Mike's ticket.

46:04.790 --> 46:06.870
Stay close to the resources,
the juice.

46:07.070 --> 46:09.290
If you're sure, I can get you
on a cutaway shot.

46:09.490 --> 46:12.080
I know it's a risk
taking on the party machinery.

46:12.280 --> 46:15.690
I'm not just going to be some
schmo out in the wilderness...

46:15.890 --> 46:17.690
in a run for Congress.

46:18.230 --> 46:20.420
We're live.

46:20.620 --> 46:26.110
In five, four, three...

46:27.240 --> 46:29.160


46:34.330 --> 46:35.860
I'm Mike Prince.

46:36.050 --> 46:37.960
If you only follow
the primaries,

46:38.160 --> 46:39.530
you don't know me.

46:39.720 --> 46:40.840
That's by design.

46:41.040 --> 46:44.960
So the status quo can keep
a hold of your futures.

46:45.670 --> 46:47.910
I bought this time
and it didn't come cheap

46:48.110 --> 46:49.870
because I'm my own man.

46:50.070 --> 46:51.870
And because we need
to have a hard conversation

46:52.070 --> 46:56.890
about why both parties,
and our system, are broken.

46:57.770 --> 47:00.070
This is about the inventory
we all need to take

47:00.270 --> 47:02.550
in order to get
where we're going,

47:02.750 --> 47:05.360
even if we don't
always like what we see.

47:06.070 --> 47:08.950


47:10.820 --> 47:12.490
[door closes]

47:18.910 --> 47:20.690
[Krakow] Grigor.

47:20.890 --> 47:23.320
Buddy, you're back.

47:23.520 --> 47:26.720
You are surprised
to see me here?

47:26.920 --> 47:29.830
I'm surprised
to see you here as well,

47:30.030 --> 47:31.870
since four of
the last five nights,

47:32.070 --> 47:36.420
you've been spotted outside
Oksana's penthouse.

47:36.620 --> 47:38.730
My penthouse, not your own.

47:38.930 --> 47:41.150
She's been distraught
in your absence.

47:41.350 --> 47:42.710
I've tried to counsel her.

47:42.910 --> 47:45.360
Tell her to, you know, hang in.

47:45.560 --> 47:48.890
This is why I brought you
a special gift.

47:49.090 --> 47:51.410
You should open it now.

47:51.610 --> 47:56.580
Might come in handy
in case you need to "hang in."

47:56.780 --> 48:01.190
My friend Christian
designed them personally.

48:01.390 --> 48:02.980
Gossamer wings.

48:03.180 --> 48:06.720
Now, I cannot tell you
if they support flights,

48:06.920 --> 48:09.950
since I didn't test them
myself, but...

48:10.150 --> 48:13.720
Since you live
on the 29th floor,

48:13.920 --> 48:18.330
maybe you would
like to be the test pilot.

48:18.530 --> 48:21.540
You could have sent this
message in so many ways,

48:21.740 --> 48:23.380
without coming to New York.

48:23.580 --> 48:27.130
What fucking fun would there be
in letting someone else

48:27.330 --> 48:29.720
throw you out the window?

48:29.920 --> 48:32.640
I swear, Oksana and I
are just friends.

48:32.840 --> 48:33.850
W-we're not even friends.

48:34.050 --> 48:35.890
It was just a--a mere
business arrangement--

48:36.090 --> 48:39.940
But you spent so many months
in her company.

48:40.140 --> 48:41.560
I'll never see her again.

48:41.760 --> 48:42.980
I'll stop funding
the divorce action.

48:43.180 --> 48:45.710
In fact, I'll end it
with one fucking phone call.

48:45.910 --> 48:48.920
It's hard to argue
abandonment now anyway.

48:49.420 --> 48:51.530
This is good news.

48:51.730 --> 48:55.660
It clears the way
for my own divorce suit...

48:55.860 --> 48:58.890
on grounds of adultery.

49:01.310 --> 49:02.980
Thank you.

49:08.900 --> 49:11.400


49:19.740 --> 49:21.290
[sighs]

49:26.750 --> 49:32.300
My business is concluded.
Now, yours can begin.

49:33.260 --> 49:35.120
It's quite a favor
Axe granted you.

49:35.320 --> 49:37.270
And that you granted him.

49:37.470 --> 49:38.970
[dry chuckle]

49:39.890 --> 49:42.210
How the hell did you two
become friends again,

49:42.410 --> 49:43.900
after what he did to you?

49:44.100 --> 49:46.900
Well, one has
the greatest respect

49:47.100 --> 49:49.720
for one's fiercest adversary.

49:49.910 --> 49:54.700
Who else believes so strongly
in your abilities?

49:56.150 --> 49:59.160
Well, it's time.
You ready to do the turn?

49:59.360 --> 50:02.490
Like Andre in '87.

50:04.410 --> 50:07.580


50:08.290 --> 50:10.670
[engine starts]

50:25.480 --> 50:28.020


50:31.060 --> 50:33.030
[police sirens chirp]

50:34.320 --> 50:36.780
[sirens blaring]

50:38.490 --> 50:40.370
[sirens stop]

50:41.070 --> 50:43.410
[indistinct chatter]

50:47.080 --> 50:49.300
Let's go. Out of the car.

50:49.500 --> 50:52.820
